Shares of JPMorgan (JPM.N ) and Bank of America (BAC.N) rose more than half a percent, helping the S&P financial index gain .SPSY 0.65%. American Express (AXP.N) rose 1.5% and was the biggest boost to the Dow Jones Industrial Average. DJI, which was up 0.21% at 24.926.47 points. Markets were battered this week by fears of trade war after reports that President Donald Trump was planning to impose tariffs on Chinese imports and the ouster of Secretary of State Rex Tillerson.

